body:
Workarounds are currently possible, e.g. [`tensorflow_ros`](https://github.com/tradr-project/tensorflow_ros/) links against the pip binaries for C++.

The only limitation is that the current pip binaries are built with the old C++ ABI, while some OS (e.g. Ubuntu 16) build only with the new C++11 ABI. There's a [pip bug report](https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/python-pip/+bug/1707002) about that. 
@asimshankar Is this going to be solved at some point ?
